summary: This is an FBI Electronic Surveillance (ELSUR) evidence envelope form documenting the transfer of intercepted communications evidence, likely related to the Epstein investigation. The form indicates it contains original magnetic tape evidence from a Title III court-authorized intercept or consensual monitoring.
keyFacts: The document is an FBI ELSUR evidence envelope form used for tracking intercepted communications evidence.
It references a Title III court-authorized intercept or consensual monitoring, indicating legally obtained surveillance.
The evidence medium is an original magnetic tape, suggesting audio recordings from telephone or other intercepts.
Multiple custody signatures and dates indicate chain of custody documentation for the evidence.
